Package: cat.llm
Title: LLM-Powered Text Classification for Social Science
Version: 3.0.0
Authors@R: person("Chris", "Soria", email = "chrissoria@berkeley.edu",
                  role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Meta-package that installs and loads the full CatLLM ecosystem
    for LLM-powered text classification across domains. Installing cat.llm
    brings in cat.stack (general-purpose engine), cat.survey (survey responses),
    cat.vader (social media), cat.ademic (academic papers), and cat.cog
    (cognitive assessment). Like the tidyverse, you can install the full
    ecosystem or individual domain packages.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/chrissoria/cat-llm
BugReports: https://github.com/chrissoria/cat-llm/issues
Depends:
    R (>= 3.5.0)
Imports:
    cat.stack (>= 0.1.0),
    cat.survey (>= 0.1.0),
    cat.vader (>= 0.1.0),
    cat.ademic (>= 0.1.0),
    cat.cog (>= 0.1.0),
    reticulate (>= 1.28)
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Encoding: UTF-8
